issue.title: i.w.t. run this server in docker containers [WIP]
issue.body:
If applied, this PR will:
- [x] Add `docker-compose.yml` to the project
- [x] Add `Dockerfile` to define node container with SatelliteSpotter builtit
- [x] Creates a container arrangement with a node.js container and Postgres container connected on their own network config. Running docker-compose will launch the server and is open on port 80 (`localhost:80` will hit endpoint)
- [ ] Import csv data on container start

To run (on a computer with docker):
- `git clone`
- `git checkout feature/dockerize`
- `cd <project-dir>/server`
- Edit `Dockerfile` and replace `<add dir here>` with the absolute path to the `server` directory 
- `docker-compose up`

To Stop: 
- press control-c *twice*
- `docker-compose down --rmi all`
